amily:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I have answered each below.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I have set no targets for Dyfed-Powys Police, except the basic mission of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">cutting crime.  This was a conscious decision as I believe that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">target</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s tend to distort </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">incentives and result in unintended outcomes. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Being a rural force area, with low crime figures, our data is often subject to huge variation. Relatively small changes in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> absolute numbers lead to large percentage shifts. This has two effects. It makes figures easier to manipulate. Secondly, it means even pure figures do not necessarily reflect performance as experienced by the public. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I have instead </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">emphasised quality of s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ervice and professionalism </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">amongst</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">officers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, which my Chief Constable is pressing hard on the Force.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I believe this has begun to reduce pressure on the system to produce favourable figures and encouraged better professional judgment. This may result in cr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ime figures rising</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. I will monitor this very carefully</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">am</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> prepared to accept this if it provides a better reflection of reality.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Target-based performance culture is deeply embedded within the police. Changing it will take time and leadership. My Chief </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Constable is committed to improving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">leadership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and I have agreed to investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to this end</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">where necessary. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I do not expect crime and detection recording practices to change fast</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, however.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I treat them with studied scepticism. We </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">provide assurance by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">scrutinising</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">rime statistics in conjunction with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">other qualitative measures</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> incl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">uding public confidence and victim satisfaction measures</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> from independent sources such as the Crime Survey for England and Wales</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, media coverage, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">surveys </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and public engagemen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">t feedback</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Since taking up office I have sought to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">increase the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">transparency </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">of police performance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">We</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> hold monthly performance boards and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> have established</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> an Out of Court Disposal Scrutiny Panel, which assess</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">es the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> use of cautions. The Chief Constabl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">e and I are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">exploring</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> partnership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> with academia, with College of Policing backing, to improve the quality of our performance work. This will bring greater independence, breadth and analysis to assessments of police and local criminal justice system perfor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">mance.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Crime statistics will always be subject to political and organisational pressure. They </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">are undoubtedly useful but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">must be treated with caution and understood in context. They must also be considered alongside other information, particularly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">qualitative assessments.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; mar